INSERT INTO `op_article_article` VALUES (8, 7, 4, 1, 'en', '2006-06-20 17:44:00', '2006-06-20 17:44:47', '2006-06-26 16:09:29', 0, 0, 'RPC', '', '', '', '', '<p>The file <b>rpcserver.php</b> in the root folder is a server which handles xml rpc requests.  <a href="http://www.xmlrpc.com/" target="_blank">RPC</a>\r\nis a spec and a set of implementations that allow software running on\r\ndisparate operating systems, running in different environments to make\r\nprocedure calls over the Internet. </p>     <p>  Smart3 uses the PEAR <a href="http://pear.php.net/package/XML_RPC/" target="_blank">XML RPC</a> library<span class="surname">. You can find a test view in the <b>/views_rpcserver</b>\r\nfolder which serves the latest published or modified articles. Currently there is only one view to test. With this view it is\r\npossible to fetch the latest modified or published articles from a\r\nwebsite. <a href="#example">Below</a>  on this page you can see an RPC call example. Therefore this page uses an other view helper class in which you can find an action call to the remote server delivered with this package. See:</span></p><p>/views_home/ViewArticleRpc.php</p><p>/templates_home/tpl.ArticleRPC.php&nbsp;</p><p><span class="surname">You can also test the server from withhin an other php application through the Rpc-Client in <a href="tests/XmlRpcClient.php" target="_blank">/tests/XmlRpcClient.php</a>.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Example:<a title="example" name="example"></a></h4><p>Fetch the latest published articles of this site through RPC </p>', '', '', '');
