INSERT INTO `op_article_index` VALUES (7, ' Ajax    Asynchronous JavaScript And XML, or its acronym Ajax\r\n(Pronounced A-JAX), is a Web development technique for creating\r\ninteractive web applications. The intent is to shift a great deal of\r\ninteraction to the Web surfer&#39;s computer, exchanging data with the\r\nserver behind the scenes, so that the entire Web page does not have to\r\nbe reloaded each time the user makes a change. This is meant to\r\nincrease the Web page&#39;s interactivity, speed, and usability. (Wikipedia)For Ajax examples see bellow.&nbsp;Smart3 makes use of the PEAR Ajax_HTML\r\nlibrary from Joshua Eichhorn. The integration is very experimental.&nbsp;\r\nAjax_HTML is still in alpha stage and the Smart3 developer(s) have just\r\nstarted to understand the Ajax technology.Smart3 let the choice to the project developers to use Ajax or not. Ajax is an optionally feature. The\r\ndifficulty with the Ajax-Technology isnt the technical part but rather\r\nthe usabillity part. Users generally expect that clicking the back\r\nbutton in web applications will undo their last state change and in\r\nAjax applications this might not be the case.The ajax\r\nintegration consists of a server and a client part. This means, the\r\nclient can execute server side php code through javascript functions.\r\nThe result can be displayed in parts of the current webpage without\r\nreloading the whole page. To get work ajax, you have to include in the client html template the ajax server: &lsaquo;script type=&#39;text/javascript&#39;         src=&#39;ajaxserver.php?client=all&amp;amp;stub=all&amp;amp;view=articleAjax&#39;&rsaquo;&lsaquo;/script&rsaquo;The\r\nvariable &quot;view=articleAjax&quot; define which view class contains the ajax\r\nmethods that can be accessed through javascript functions. In this case\r\nit is the class in the file /views_home/ViewArticleAjax.php.\r\nFuthermore the html template has to include some javascript init code:&nbsp;&lt;script type=&#39;text/javascript&#39; src=&#39;templates_home/ArticleAjax.js&#39;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;Now\r\nyou can execute through the javascript functions server side php code.\r\nFor a detailed description consult the following files for this page:/templates_home/tpl.ArticleAjax.php&nbsp; (HTML template of this page)/templates_home/ArticleAjax.js (Javascript init) /views_home/ViewArticleAjax.php (PHP class with the ajax methods)\r\nExamples  ', '', '', '');
