INSERT INTO `op_misc_text` VALUES (1, 2, 'Text of the index page', '', '<p>Welcome to the Open Publisher Content Mangement System (CMS).  If you have chosen  &quot;insert example content&quot; during the setup proceedure you should see this message and  some example  content text.  The example default templates and content give you an overviev  of how you can  organize content and how to  present this content on a public web  project. </p><p>One feature of the CMS Open Publisher, which concists of a couple of modules that are based on the framework <a href="http://www.smart3.org" target="_blank">Smart3</a>, is flexibility. You are not forced to present the content  in a specific order and layout. But this means also that you have to understand how the system works. The default templates, css files and view-helper classes show you one way how this example content can be presented to a web visitor. </p><h3>The example content</h3><p>Usually the content (Articles, links,....); text, images, files is organized in a node (categories) structure. In such a structure you can manage thousands of articles with attached images and files. Therefore Open Publisher provides nodes and articles management modules. The <a href="index.php?id_node=1">Lorem Ipsum</a>  node (category) show you how such organized content (articles) is organized. There is one layout for the nodes and one for the articles.</p><p><i>See the html templates and the related view helper classes:</i></p><ul><li>templates_home/tpl.Node.php</li><li>templates_home/tpl.Article.php</li><li>views_home/ViewNode.php</li><li>views_home/ViewArticle.php</li></ul><p>The <a href="index.php?id_node=6">Support</a>  node uses an other template and view helper class (means: content is organized in a different order) because this node only contains one article with no subnodes. </p><p><i> See the template and related view helper cass for this node and article:</i></p><ul><li>templates_home/tpl.SimpleNodeArticle.php</li><li>templates_home/ViewSimpleNodeArticle.php</li></ul><p>The <a href="index.php?id_node=2">Blog</a>  node contains only one subnodes level with articles. A blog entry is nothing else than an article with attached comments.</p><p><i> See the template and related view helper cass for this node and article:</i></p><ul><li>templates_home/tpl.BlogMain.php</li><li>templates_home/tpl.Article.php</li><li>views_home/ViewBlogMain.php</li><li>views_home/ViewArticle.php</li></ul><p>This <a href="index.php">text</a> , that you are reading, is part of the content which isnt organized in the nodes structure. You can manage such content in the <b>misc text management module</b>. </p><p><i> See the template and related view helper cass for this text:</i></p><ul><li>templates_home/tpl.Index.php</li><li>templates_home/ViewIndex.php</li></ul><br /><p>The text of the right border of the public page is also such a misc text.</p><p><i> See the template and related view helper cass for this text:</i></p>\r\n<ul><li>templates_home/tpl.RightBorder.php</li><li>templates_home/ViewRightBorder.php</li></ul><br /><p>&nbsp;</p>', 0, '');
